WEBVTT

00:06.833 --> 00:11.458
 I'm keeping you safe
because remember, I love you, New York.

00:13.542 --> 00:16.207
You're giving yourself
a lot of emergency power.

00:16.208 --> 00:20.166
Your Safer Streets initiative
equates vigilantes with terrorists.

00:20.167 --> 00:23.624
<i>They took my</i> tía. <i>The Task Force.
People usually disappear after that.</i>

00:23.625 --> 00:25.957
<i>I vowed to clean up the streets,
and I did.</i>

00:28.667 --> 00:30.999
You're being held
under the Safer Streets Act.

00:31.000 --> 00:32.374
You're not at Rikers.

00:32.375 --> 00:34.666
The NYPD has no jurisdiction
over this place,

00:34.667 --> 00:36.416
or any idea of your whereabouts.

00:36.417 --> 00:39.666
Kirsten, plead out.
Avoid losing the Duquesne case.

00:39.667 --> 00:41.082
Oh, Ben, fuck you.

00:41.083 --> 00:43.707
<i>Now you've got a ship
capsized in the East River.</i>

00:43.708 --> 00:45.999
<i>I could put together
a little night crew</i>

00:46.000 --> 00:47.291
<i>from all over the world.</i>

00:47.292 --> 00:49.167
<i>He's using the Freeport
to smuggle arms.</i>

00:53.417 --> 00:55.874
 <i>If Fisk moves those guns
into Red Hook, they vanish.</i>

00:55.875 --> 00:57.541
<i>I have something to show you.</i>

01:00.542 --> 01:03.625
<i>They're hunting us.
Maybe it's time we started hunting them.</i>

01:33.667 --> 01:34.916
What choice did I have?

01:34.917 --> 01:37.250
Sit there and wait for them
to come in shooting?

01:38.167 --> 01:39.667
Look, I did a little recon.

01:40.917 --> 01:41.999
Recon?

01:45.375 --> 01:47.166
What-- What is going on with you?

01:47.167 --> 01:48.792
This is how we end it.

01:49.417 --> 01:51.625
- By kidnapping Task Force?
- What if it works?

01:52.875 --> 01:55.042
Look, the reason that
I brought him here is...

01:55.667 --> 01:58.083
I'm telling you,
something's different about him.

01:59.667 --> 02:00.792
Different how?

02:12.375 --> 02:13.792
Hey, wait, wait, wait, wait.

02:14.333 --> 02:16.249
You're wrong. I was looking for you.

02:16.250 --> 02:17.417
- Yeah, to kill us.
- No!

02:17.792 --> 02:20.457
Whatever you... The Resistance is,

02:20.458 --> 02:22.791
- I want to help.
- Bullshit. It's a trap.

02:22.792 --> 02:24.624
- No. No, it's not--
- Talk. Talk!

02:24.625 --> 02:26.832
Powell, the rest of them, they're psychos.

02:26.833 --> 02:29.457
You either go with them or you're dead.

02:31.542 --> 02:33.749
What Fisk is doing to you guys,

02:33.750 --> 02:35.291
hunting you, it's wrong!

02:35.292 --> 02:37.374
- You're lying. You're a liar.
- I'm not lying.

02:37.375 --> 02:39.083
- You are lying to us.
- I'm not!

02:40.042 --> 02:41.542
Yeah, he's telling the truth.

02:41.792 --> 02:42.792
Okay.

02:43.583 --> 02:45.708
So you wanna help us. So what?

02:46.208 --> 02:47.874
I'm part of a detail

02:47.875 --> 02:49.666
at Red Hook. Okay?

02:49.667 --> 02:51.416
We're watching the <i>Northern Star.</i>

02:51.417 --> 02:52.625
Check my left pocket.

02:57.792 --> 02:59.499
That will get you in everywhere.

02:59.500 --> 03:01.667
But the code changes at midnight, daily.

03:05.167 --> 03:06.999
- You're lying to me.
- I'm not lying.

03:07.000 --> 03:08.375
- You're lying.
- I'm not lying.

03:09.125 --> 03:10.208
Look at me.

03:13.167 --> 03:14.167
What's your name?

03:15.083 --> 03:16.083
Saunders.

03:16.792 --> 03:18.500
- Alan Saunders.
- Okay, Alan.

03:20.083 --> 03:21.458
The hood's going back on.

03:22.500 --> 03:23.750
I'm gonna hit you hard.

03:24.333 --> 03:25.416
It's gonna hurt.

03:25.417 --> 03:26.958
Karen will take you outside.

03:27.375 --> 03:29.250
Tell your squad I beat you down.

03:31.833 --> 03:33.583
If you're lying to me, you fuck,

03:34.458 --> 03:35.458
I'll find you.

03:36.625 --> 03:37.708
And I'll be unhappy.

03:39.875 --> 03:40.875
I'm not.

03:42.583 --> 03:44.332
You've got to stop Fisk.

03:44.333 --> 03:45.917
You're the only one who can--

06:07.750 --> 06:08.917
One...

06:13.958 --> 06:15.000
...two...

06:18.167 --> 06:19.792
three.

06:38.250 --> 06:39.332
Kirsten.

06:39.333 --> 06:40.541
Hey, Heather.

06:40.542 --> 06:42.416
- Are you okay?
- Uh, no.

06:42.417 --> 06:45.042
Hochberg pulled the trial up by two weeks,
so I'm pissed.

06:46.042 --> 06:47.042
I didn't know.

06:47.458 --> 06:49.582
You're seriously making this more awkward?

06:49.583 --> 06:52.833
I read your psych eval on Duquesne.
It's a hatchet job.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.125
These men you're defending...

06:55.667 --> 06:57.374
are dangerous. Don't you see that?

06:57.375 --> 06:58.832
Frank Castle is a murderer.

06:58.833 --> 07:00.749
Him and Daredevil might've killed Matt.

07:00.750 --> 07:02.874
Or he was working with them, I don't know.

07:02.875 --> 07:03.957
Heather, I--

07:03.958 --> 07:05.958
I don't think that that's what happened.

07:07.375 --> 07:08.875
In my gut, I just...

07:10.083 --> 07:12.082
Matt was a liar about so many things.

07:12.083 --> 07:14.500
I don't know what to believe
when it comes to him.

07:17.542 --> 07:18.708
He lied to you, too.

07:21.333 --> 07:22.375
You're right.

07:23.667 --> 07:24.750
You're right.

07:26.083 --> 07:27.583
And, yeah, Matt was...

07:29.250 --> 07:31.708
Is complicated.

07:33.583 --> 07:35.124
But he's a good man

07:35.125 --> 07:39.666
who's probably in serious danger
because of Wilson Fisk.

07:39.667 --> 07:41.874
Honestly, Kirsten, as your friend,

07:41.875 --> 07:44.166
I don't think you're seeing
any of this clearly.

07:44.167 --> 07:46.124
Why would you work for Fisk?

07:46.125 --> 07:47.333
Because...

07:47.792 --> 07:50.583
he's genuinely trying to
make this city a safer place.

07:51.583 --> 07:55.166
I was on the other end of that
vigilante violence, you weren't.

07:55.167 --> 07:56.582
- Heather--
- You weren't here

07:56.583 --> 07:58.457
when Matt disappeared. So, unless

07:58.458 --> 08:02.874
some maniac in a mask is trying to
cut you open, don't judge me.

08:02.875 --> 08:04.333
Hey. Hey.

08:05.083 --> 08:06.792
I am really sorry

08:07.250 --> 08:08.791
for what happened to you.

08:08.792 --> 08:09.792
I am.

08:11.792 --> 08:13.125
Fisk isn't the answer.

08:17.750 --> 08:20.457
If you don't mind,
I have to go defend a "dangerous man"

08:20.458 --> 08:23.375
against an entire system
hell-bent on putting him away.

08:58.333 --> 09:00.750
<i>HQ, checking
confirmation clearance on gate.</i>

09:12.542 --> 09:13.625
Come on, step out.

09:18.167 --> 09:19.208
Stop.

09:20.500 --> 09:21.500
This way.

09:22.333 --> 09:24.374
- Can I take this thing off?
- Nope.

09:25.833 --> 09:27.125
You need to watch your step.

09:32.917 --> 09:35.457
You know, you're breaking
ten different laws here.

09:35.458 --> 09:39.374
This isn't how "reasonable access
to legal counsel" is supposed to go.

09:39.375 --> 09:40.749
Your client's a terrorist--

09:40.750 --> 09:43.041
That requires
a staggering burden of proof.

09:43.042 --> 09:44.375
Fuckin' lawyers. Look,

09:44.958 --> 09:46.249
you're getting your visit.

09:46.250 --> 09:48.000
No need to give me shit about it.

09:48.917 --> 09:50.000
Besides, ma'am...

09:51.000 --> 09:52.458
I'm just trying to do my job.

10:13.083 --> 10:14.332
Stop.

10:17.667 --> 10:19.708
Forward.

10:24.792 --> 10:25.792
Forward.

10:29.333 --> 10:30.333
Stop.

10:30.875 --> 10:32.000
Remove the goggles.

10:32.542 --> 10:33.542
Finally.

10:34.542 --> 10:36.042
You got 15 minutes.

10:36.750 --> 10:37.792
Don't try shit.

10:40.458 --> 10:41.667
That goes for you, too.

10:45.292 --> 10:46.458
Mr. Duquesne.

10:48.417 --> 10:50.250
It's a pleasure to finally meet you.

10:52.083 --> 10:55.416
I'm surprised they agreed to
such legal niceties.

10:55.417 --> 10:58.667
Well, I filed about
a dozen separate legal briefs.

10:59.542 --> 11:01.874
Most of them question
the validity of this trial.

11:01.875 --> 11:03.417
I think you mean tribunal.

11:04.792 --> 11:05.792
Yeah.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.082
It's a mess.

11:08.083 --> 11:11.124
At least Hochberg
agreed to this... meeting.

11:11.125 --> 11:13.417
He doesn't want to
set a precedent this early.

11:15.250 --> 11:16.750
So, I'm the first, aren't I?

11:18.250 --> 11:19.332
Yeah, you are.

11:19.333 --> 11:22.583
Which means I have no idea
how this is gonna go.

11:23.625 --> 11:24.625
- Sorry.
- Well...

11:25.333 --> 11:28.083
I imagine it will be quite a spectacle.

11:29.167 --> 11:31.957
Fisk needs this. A public show.

11:31.958 --> 11:34.832
<i>Les guillotines
sur la Place de la Nation.</i>

11:34.833 --> 11:38.875
To think, this started out
as just a garden-variety shakedown.

11:39.375 --> 11:40.375
Shakedown?

11:40.875 --> 11:44.208
Fisk wanted me to
invest in his port project.

11:44.958 --> 11:45.958
I refused,

11:46.417 --> 11:47.417
<i>et voilà.</i>

11:47.958 --> 11:50.167
If this was really about vigilantes,

11:50.542 --> 11:53.291
I think he'd go after more than just
his personal enemies.

11:53.292 --> 11:55.291
If Fisk can prove you're the Swordsman,

11:55.292 --> 11:57.541
he'll take what he wants,
and the law allows it.

11:57.542 --> 11:59.749
"Forfeiture of a criminal's assets."

11:59.750 --> 12:02.875
You know, the similarities
to the Reign of Terror never cease.

12:03.875 --> 12:06.124
So, when do they loot St. Patrick's now?

12:06.125 --> 12:07.541
I think it's on Tuesday.

12:07.542 --> 12:08.750
Perfect.

12:09.375 --> 12:11.833
The thing is, I've seen the discovery.

12:13.083 --> 12:16.375
The district attorney has no proof
you are who Fisk says you are.

12:17.958 --> 12:20.125
Do they need that these days, Counselor?

12:21.417 --> 12:22.417
I don't know.

12:24.875 --> 12:26.208
I really don't know.

12:26.958 --> 12:28.041
Hey, over here!

12:28.042 --> 12:29.457
- Hey!
-  Help!

12:29.458 --> 12:31.124
-  Move!
- Somebody help us!

12:31.125 --> 12:32.625
- Help.
-  Help me!

12:33.167 --> 12:35.124
- Help me!
-  Somebody help, please!

12:38.000 --> 12:39.000
Help!

12:39.833 --> 12:40.833
Help me!

12:45.167 --> 12:46.582
Please help us!

12:46.583 --> 12:47.958
Somebody help me!

12:57.042 --> 12:58.624
You're turning into Frank.

13:00.958 --> 13:02.083
Well, he always said,

13:02.500 --> 13:04.833
- "Know your enemy, they're all you have."
- Yeah.

13:05.708 --> 13:07.250
Sounds extremely Frank.

13:09.958 --> 13:11.124
You think he's dead?

13:11.125 --> 13:12.208
No, not a chance.

13:12.583 --> 13:15.707
If he was, Fisk would hang his corpse
off the Brooklyn Bridge.

13:15.708 --> 13:17.083
Taking out the Punisher?

13:18.125 --> 13:19.874
He'd sing that from the rooftops.

13:19.875 --> 13:22.250
So, what? So, he's just...

13:23.208 --> 13:24.958
All this, he's just out there just...

13:25.375 --> 13:26.457
being him.

13:26.458 --> 13:27.667
Same as always.

13:28.583 --> 13:30.292
I don't know.

13:31.083 --> 13:32.749
He's always been there for me.

13:32.750 --> 13:34.249
For us, before, so...

13:37.833 --> 13:39.583
Well, what are you, uh...

13:41.542 --> 13:42.957
You want his help?

13:42.958 --> 13:43.958
Well, I mean...

13:45.958 --> 13:47.458
he is effective.

13:53.333 --> 13:56.333
You realize murder is not how we win this?

14:04.917 --> 14:06.707
- Karen?
- Jesus Christ. Okay.

14:06.708 --> 14:08.791
Okay. Of course. I am not suggesting

14:08.792 --> 14:11.792
that we go out and start murdering
random Task Force, but...

14:12.625 --> 14:14.124
cutting the head off the snake?

14:14.125 --> 14:16.000
Does killing Fisk bring Foggy back?

14:17.417 --> 14:18.625
Would he have wanted that?

14:20.792 --> 14:22.917
Trust me, I wonder
the same thing every day.

14:24.250 --> 14:27.083
Vanessa killed Foggy and nothing happened.

14:27.458 --> 14:28.707
Fisk got elected,

14:28.708 --> 14:30.832
he turns the whole city
into his piggy bank,

14:30.833 --> 14:33.749
guarded by thugs with badges,
and nothing fucking happened.

14:33.750 --> 14:36.083
- I know.
- It just feels like we are up against...

14:36.500 --> 14:38.832
so much.

14:38.833 --> 14:40.416
And we still have a system

14:40.417 --> 14:42.042
that is not entirely broken.

14:42.750 --> 14:43.750
Yeah.

14:47.125 --> 14:49.000
Are you sure the Governor got a copy?

14:50.750 --> 14:51.833
<i>I am.</i>

14:59.000 --> 15:00.332
Where did this come from?

15:00.333 --> 15:01.416
Anonymous.

15:01.417 --> 15:02.499
Come on, Gomez.

15:02.500 --> 15:05.208
Nothing's anonymous.
Especially not a document like that.

15:11.333 --> 15:14.207
You sic your
CIA friend on my Attorney General.

15:14.208 --> 15:15.917
You refuse financial assistance.

15:16.792 --> 15:18.917
You're trying to avoid state oversight.

15:20.250 --> 15:22.457
If I need help, I will ask.

15:22.458 --> 15:24.666
It was a deft move, developing Red Hook,

15:24.667 --> 15:26.416
knowing its status as a free port

15:26.417 --> 15:29.500
would lead to incredible profits
with minimal accountability.

15:30.667 --> 15:32.582
I understand that Fisk Industries

15:32.583 --> 15:34.666
and your wife Vanessa
are major shareholders.

15:34.667 --> 15:37.249
All of it transferred into a trust

15:37.250 --> 15:38.791
when I took office.

15:38.792 --> 15:40.999
All the paperwork, completely legal.

15:41.000 --> 15:43.166
I have no doubt. But money and...

15:43.167 --> 15:45.875
an army of white-shoe lawyers
doesn't make you immune.

15:46.167 --> 15:47.167
Well...

15:47.583 --> 15:49.457
still no idea what's inside Red Hook.

15:49.458 --> 15:51.583
New construction had
no blueprints, at least...

15:52.333 --> 15:53.708
none that we could steal.

15:56.958 --> 15:58.208
Okay. So...

16:00.167 --> 16:01.249
you get inside,

16:01.250 --> 16:02.832
- then what?
- I torch the weapons.

16:02.833 --> 16:04.792
- Oh, my God.
- Make a big noise.

16:05.208 --> 16:07.500
You get your sources
to put it out there, and...

16:08.333 --> 16:10.833
we force everyone in New York
to see who he is,

16:11.667 --> 16:12.750
to know what he does.

16:13.417 --> 16:16.124
You know, I recently received a copy

16:16.125 --> 16:18.041
of the <i>Charter of 1855.</i>

16:18.042 --> 16:21.499
The Freeport status is
perpetual and inviolable.

16:21.500 --> 16:24.124
It can only be revoked
by the order of the Governor.

16:24.125 --> 16:29.250
Well, I sincerely hope for New York's sake
that you're not considering such a thing.

16:29.833 --> 16:31.583
The Governor will have to revoke it.

16:34.125 --> 16:35.125
I'm gonna be okay.

16:35.833 --> 16:38.292
You don't know that. You don't know that.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.333
Every time you go out,
there's no guarantee you return.

16:43.833 --> 16:46.207
<i>Mayor Fisk, I've turned a blind eye</i>

16:46.208 --> 16:48.124
to your Emergency Powers,

16:48.125 --> 16:50.625
Safer Streets, Vigilante Trials,
because...

16:51.042 --> 16:54.416
on paper, and with most of
the voting public, it's working.

16:54.417 --> 16:56.124
I'm glad we agree on that.

16:56.125 --> 16:57.999
I'm all for giving enough rope.

16:58.000 --> 17:00.167
But when a tanker with dubious cargo

17:00.792 --> 17:02.458
capsizes in the East River,

17:03.167 --> 17:04.792
that's when the rope pulls taut.

17:06.000 --> 17:08.999
"Dubious cargo"? I don't know
where you get your information.

17:09.000 --> 17:10.083
You don't, do you?

17:11.083 --> 17:12.125
If you'll excuse me.

17:15.083 --> 17:17.250
I'm not saying don't go, I'm just...

17:18.250 --> 17:20.250
Please, let's just be...

17:21.708 --> 17:23.292
very, very prepared.

17:39.667 --> 17:40.667
Fuck.

17:46.250 --> 17:49.541
You do realize we have the Governor's
Dinner in an hour, don't you?

17:49.542 --> 17:51.874
Yeah. First rule,
don't eat at those things.

17:51.875 --> 17:53.042
What if it's gross?

17:53.667 --> 17:55.416
You're talking, you're munching.

17:55.417 --> 17:58.417
What if you laugh and spray food
all over the Deputy Lieutenant?

17:59.750 --> 18:00.833
Not me.

18:01.917 --> 18:04.207
Besides, they're good. Try one.

18:04.208 --> 18:05.999
- I'm good.
- You're good now,

18:06.000 --> 18:07.666
but maybe try the shrimp cocktail.

18:07.667 --> 18:09.750
Thirty minutes goes by, you're sweating.

18:10.250 --> 18:12.957
Gut's about to blow.
You wanna puke on the Governor?

18:12.958 --> 18:13.958
I don't.

18:14.875 --> 18:16.208
They're dope as hell.

18:17.083 --> 18:18.750
Try one. Come on, trust me.

18:33.458 --> 18:34.458
Not bad.

18:34.667 --> 18:35.667
I told you.

18:37.333 --> 18:38.333
What's up?

18:40.417 --> 18:43.707
- What do you know about the Governor?
- You mean opposition research

18:43.708 --> 18:46.333
- from her last election?
- Well, maybe exactly that.

18:48.500 --> 18:51.332
Basically, Marge McCaffrey's
boring as fuck.

18:51.333 --> 18:53.124
Not a speck of dirt or personality.

18:53.125 --> 18:54.999
She's like a nun with a machine gun.

18:55.000 --> 18:56.749
Played it perfectly for decades.

18:56.750 --> 18:58.374
She won't drop a stitch now.

18:58.375 --> 18:59.708
Everyone's hiding something.

19:00.458 --> 19:03.916
That's why I'm getting
the Lieutenant Governor loose and talking.

19:03.917 --> 19:07.916
What, and you think he'll give you,
a total stranger, his secrets, do you?

19:07.917 --> 19:09.541
I got you to eat street meat.

19:09.542 --> 19:11.083
What do you think's in there?

19:14.875 --> 19:15.875
You got any tips?

19:16.542 --> 19:17.542
Excuse me?

19:20.667 --> 19:23.792
I'm sure you learnt
some interrogation skills up at, you know,

19:24.208 --> 19:25.292
Herefordshire.

19:27.250 --> 19:28.999
I'm sorry, where?

19:29.000 --> 19:31.332
Come on, you were a squaddie, right?

19:31.333 --> 19:34.000
I mean, Special Air Service
for Her Majesty?

19:34.750 --> 19:36.124
Special Ops?

19:36.125 --> 19:37.542
Don't look so shocked.

19:38.375 --> 19:39.542
I get intel, too.

19:40.792 --> 19:42.041
How high are you now?

19:42.042 --> 19:43.042
No, I'm...

19:43.583 --> 19:45.167
I'm not high right now.

19:45.750 --> 19:47.917
Have you considered using these, um...

19:48.708 --> 19:50.457
intelligence skills to find out

19:50.458 --> 19:52.374
who's feeding the "City Without Fear"?

19:52.375 --> 19:53.707
Yeah, I'm on it.

19:53.708 --> 19:55.625
- I told you, I'm on it.
- Good.

19:57.375 --> 20:00.332
'Cause you wouldn't want
the squaddie stealing your kill.

20:02.458 --> 20:03.792
- No.
- No.

20:06.083 --> 20:07.917
Whoever is mocking the mayor

20:08.667 --> 20:10.292
must be punished, correct?

20:11.542 --> 20:13.458
Of course. Yes, of course.

20:14.083 --> 20:16.167
I promise that I'll figure out who it is.

20:18.875 --> 20:19.875
Great.

20:23.667 --> 20:26.000
He really hates that mask, doesn't he?

20:30.542 --> 20:32.291
- Wouldn't you?
- I don't know.

20:32.292 --> 20:35.499
I mean, getting roasted like that
is kinda flattering.

20:35.500 --> 20:36.500
No.

20:37.792 --> 20:39.000
It's not flattering.

20:40.583 --> 20:41.708
Find out who it is,

20:42.500 --> 20:43.792
turn them to me.

20:44.292 --> 20:45.292
All sorted.

20:47.958 --> 20:49.125
Right.

20:56.667 --> 20:58.582
 It's me again!

20:58.583 --> 21:01.749
Your favorite Mayor Kingpin,

21:01.750 --> 21:04.457
here to make a better New York.

21:04.458 --> 21:06.916
<i>Look at this guy and his puny sword.</i>

21:06.917 --> 21:08.791
<i>He calls himself "The Swordsman"?</i>

21:08.792 --> 21:10.916
Don't worry, size doesn't matter,

21:10.917 --> 21:13.416
said no swordsman ever!

21:13.417 --> 21:15.541
But now that I've got him,

21:15.542 --> 21:20.374
he's going to have a hard time
"swording out" his problems.

21:22.292 --> 21:25.624
<i>Jack Duquesne,
this bargain basement Zorro,</i>

21:25.625 --> 21:28.624
thinks he's such a great guy,
donating millions of dollars

21:28.625 --> 21:31.207
<i>to lame places like children's hospitals</i>

21:31.208 --> 21:33.499
and woman shelters. Woof.

21:33.500 --> 21:35.749
<i>Swordsman, another bored socialite</i>

21:35.750 --> 21:39.374
pushing his vigilante agenda
on the "weak and defenseless."

21:39.375 --> 21:44.041
Don't they know New Yorkers don't need
any protection from these masked losers

21:44.042 --> 21:45.582
because I can save them.

21:45.583 --> 21:49.875
Me and my friendly neighborhood Task Force
are here to protect you.

21:50.208 --> 21:53.041
Or throw you into a windowless box
where no one can find you.

21:53.042 --> 21:56.249
Because remember, I love you...

21:56.250 --> 21:57.457
<i>New York.</i>

22:23.333 --> 22:24.542
All rise.

22:25.917 --> 22:27.457
Sell them the truth.

22:34.625 --> 22:35.833
What's with the face?

22:37.375 --> 22:38.875
Buck up, buttercup.

22:40.625 --> 22:41.708
Come on.

22:42.708 --> 22:43.833
Let's do some good.

22:46.500 --> 22:49.666
<i>"His demeanor
is combative, hostile.</i>

22:49.667 --> 22:52.832
<i>"When challenged,
he experiences eruptions of temper,</i>

22:52.833 --> 22:56.124
"sometimes consistent with
violent episodes of mania,

22:56.125 --> 22:58.416
"like those found in violent offenders

22:58.417 --> 23:00.874
"like the recent serial killer
known as 'Muse.'"

23:00.875 --> 23:03.291
Objection. Baseless speculation,
Your Honors.

23:03.292 --> 23:07.708
Well, this is the clinical report of
a respected psychiatrist, Your Honors.

23:08.167 --> 23:10.041
Do I need to remind the defense that

23:10.042 --> 23:12.916
Dr. Glenn has extensive
firsthand experience

23:12.917 --> 23:15.124
with these kinds of violent killers?

23:15.125 --> 23:17.499
Okay. Objection!

23:17.500 --> 23:19.041
<i>Assumes facts not in evidence.</i>

23:19.042 --> 23:22.249
<i>Nowhere in this report
does Dr. Glenn say that my client</i>

23:22.250 --> 23:23.583
is a serial killer.

23:23.708 --> 23:26.499
Overruled. Mr. Hochberg,
continue with the report,

23:26.500 --> 23:28.874
and, please, do try not to editorialize.

23:28.875 --> 23:30.374
Thank you, Your Honors.

23:30.375 --> 23:32.416
 This is a mockery
of the justice system.

23:32.417 --> 23:34.999
He's crucifying Duquesne.
Everyone's buying it.

23:35.000 --> 23:36.375
No, no, not everyone.

23:37.542 --> 23:38.542
People are pissed.

23:38.958 --> 23:41.207
That's why he needs the Swordsman trial.

23:41.208 --> 23:43.499
It keeps people guessing,
keeps 'em scared.

23:43.500 --> 23:44.666
Right, right.

23:44.667 --> 23:46.457
- Hearts and minds...
- Win the war.

23:46.458 --> 23:49.249
<i>Mr. Duquesne,
I would like you to tell the court</i>

23:49.250 --> 23:50.332
<i>what you told me...</i>

23:50.333 --> 23:52.249
Hey. Hold up. Doesn't that...

23:52.250 --> 23:54.749
- Doesn't that mean...
- Somebody else got into Red Hook.

23:54.750 --> 23:56.957
Mr. Fisk had been pressuring me

23:56.958 --> 23:58.417
to fund his port project.

23:59.625 --> 24:00.832
At the Ball...

24:00.833 --> 24:03.374
- he took me aside and he threatened me.
- Objection.

24:03.375 --> 24:05.457
Irrelevant. The mayor isn't on trial.

24:05.458 --> 24:07.792
- Well, maybe he should be.
- Sustained.

24:10.417 --> 24:12.417
- Your Honors, may counsel approach?
- You may.

24:20.167 --> 24:22.541
It took me six weeks
to get access to my client,

24:22.542 --> 24:24.291
and you gave me two days' notice.

24:24.292 --> 24:27.916
We sent a scheduling change to
Ms. McDuffie's email address weeks ago.

24:27.917 --> 24:31.166
To my dead Manhattan Superior Court email.
Don't be a dick, Hochberg.

24:31.167 --> 24:33.166
Your Honors, you see what I'm up against?

24:33.167 --> 24:36.541
Thing is, Your Honor, it seems the media
had more time to prepare than I did.

24:36.542 --> 24:38.707
There is
an enormous public interest

24:38.708 --> 24:40.166
in this case, Counselor,

24:40.167 --> 24:42.416
and as you only have the afternoon,

24:42.417 --> 24:44.041
I suggest you get to your point.

24:44.042 --> 24:45.624
My point is...

24:45.625 --> 24:47.707
my client deserves a proper defense,

24:47.708 --> 24:49.875
and I have had no time to give it to him.

24:51.833 --> 24:55.833
Please allow me the latitude
to build a case for him here today.

25:05.042 --> 25:07.707
I am not unsympathetic, Ms. McDuffie.

25:07.708 --> 25:10.291
However, under
the Safer Streets initiative,

25:10.292 --> 25:11.791
our hands are tied.

25:11.792 --> 25:13.707
You know what's missing here, don't you?

25:13.708 --> 25:17.749
One single shred of proof
that my client is who you,

25:17.750 --> 25:20.207
<i>or should I say Mayor Fisk, says he is.</i>

25:20.208 --> 25:21.957
<i>- You're out of order.</i>
- Nice, Kirsten.

25:21.958 --> 25:25.999
- This isn't justice and you know it.
- You are close to contempt, Counselor.

25:34.958 --> 25:36.791
Really wish you'd taken my offer.

25:37.958 --> 25:40.541
<i>Both the people and the defense</i>

25:40.542 --> 25:42.875
<i>have presented sufficient arguments.</i>

25:43.375 --> 25:44.417
<i>Objection.</i>

25:44.833 --> 25:46.583
<i>Overruled.</i>

25:47.042 --> 25:48.917
<i>We are ready to issue a verdict.</i>

25:49.792 --> 25:51.375
Please rise, Mr. Duquesne.

25:53.083 --> 25:54.167
I'm sorry.

25:54.750 --> 25:56.917
Don't be. This was inevitable.

26:05.083 --> 26:06.208
Jack Duquesne,

26:06.708 --> 26:10.332
on the charge of conspiracy to violate
the anti-vigilante laws

26:10.333 --> 26:13.041
of the state of New York,
this court finds you guilty.

26:13.042 --> 26:15.499
A farce.

26:15.500 --> 26:16.791
Shit, get this.

26:16.792 --> 26:18.957
<i>On the charge of vigilantism,</i>

26:18.958 --> 26:20.499
which includes the repeated

26:20.500 --> 26:23.874
and willfully violent offenses of
assault and attempted murder,

26:23.875 --> 26:25.291
this court finds you guilty.

26:25.292 --> 26:27.624
For the entertainment of the masses.

26:27.625 --> 26:29.207
Sentencing will follow later.

26:29.208 --> 26:32.499
Until such time,
you will be remanded back to detention.

26:32.500 --> 26:34.124
Court's adjourned.

26:34.125 --> 26:37.207
Presented in all its ugly glory

26:37.208 --> 26:39.417
by the man whose hand holds the scale.

26:42.083 --> 26:43.208
There we go.

27:01.000 --> 27:02.083
It's starting.

27:03.292 --> 27:04.625
I'll be right there.

27:23.458 --> 27:24.999
- Sheila.
- Marge.

27:25.000 --> 27:27.875
- Sheila.
- So sorry we didn't speak earlier.

27:28.500 --> 27:30.582
- You know you were missed here.
- Oh, yeah.

27:30.583 --> 27:32.249
I'll bet. Yeah.

27:32.250 --> 27:35.666
I really wish you were with us in Albany.
I imagine you do, too.

27:35.667 --> 27:37.749
Oh... The city is my home.

27:37.750 --> 27:40.666
She obeys the alternate side parking,
and she's Governor.

27:40.667 --> 27:43.499
She's squeaky clean.
She's like Mother Teresa, okay?

27:43.500 --> 27:46.082
- The job is everything.
- Everybody's got something.

27:46.083 --> 27:48.458
And if there was something little,
you'd know.

27:49.583 --> 27:50.750
You look lovely.

27:51.917 --> 27:53.333
Your earrings are beautiful.

27:54.083 --> 27:55.167
Thank you.

27:55.792 --> 27:57.792
I hear congratulations are in order.

27:59.292 --> 28:02.332
You were instrumental
in keeping Jack Duquesne off the streets.

28:02.333 --> 28:03.542
I just did my job.

28:05.083 --> 28:07.917
Always so modest.

28:08.875 --> 28:10.875
Celebrate your successes.

28:13.000 --> 28:14.125
By the way...

28:15.000 --> 28:17.083
I put you next to Buck Cashman.

28:19.167 --> 28:21.249
Mrs. Fisk, you didn't have to do that.

28:21.250 --> 28:22.500
Probably not,

28:22.792 --> 28:24.583
but it's certainly entertaining.

28:25.167 --> 28:26.417
For you or for me?

28:28.708 --> 28:30.792
Well, that's entirely up to you.

28:41.375 --> 28:42.917
Oh. Dr. Glenn.

28:44.000 --> 28:45.292
This is a pleasant surprise.

28:45.958 --> 28:49.667
Apparently, Mrs. Fisk thinks
you need company or...

28:50.458 --> 28:51.458
a therapist.

28:53.333 --> 28:54.500
She might be right.

28:57.333 --> 28:59.332
Either way, she got us the best seats.

28:59.333 --> 29:00.333
How so?

29:01.583 --> 29:03.417
We have a perfect view of the court.

29:04.500 --> 29:06.292
As in royal court.

29:06.750 --> 29:10.042
Suitors, subjects, all swirling around.

29:12.417 --> 29:13.417
The king,

29:14.167 --> 29:17.292
of course... locking horns
with the Governor.

29:18.375 --> 29:19.375
The queen...

29:20.583 --> 29:23.208
observing everything, cataloging it...

29:24.042 --> 29:27.249
Assigning seats for inscrutable reasons.

29:27.250 --> 29:28.250
Exactly.

29:30.042 --> 29:33.041
- And we are their humble courtiers.
- Mmm.

29:33.042 --> 29:34.833
Each chosen for the...

29:35.458 --> 29:37.000
talents we possess.

29:39.542 --> 29:41.000
Like Daniel, for instance...

29:42.000 --> 29:43.000
The jester.

29:43.917 --> 29:45.792
At first glance. But...

29:46.125 --> 29:47.833
is there more than meets the eye?

29:48.500 --> 29:50.083
An heir unapparent.

29:50.583 --> 29:52.042
You like him, don't you?

29:54.042 --> 29:55.208
He's grown on me.

29:57.500 --> 29:58.792
And then we have Sheila...

29:59.542 --> 30:00.833
the chief of staff.

30:01.208 --> 30:02.332
Or...

30:02.333 --> 30:04.042
Iago...

30:05.208 --> 30:07.207
waiting with a sharpened blade.

30:10.167 --> 30:11.916
- And you?
- Me?

30:11.917 --> 30:13.167
Hmm.

30:13.625 --> 30:14.625
I'm the knight.

30:16.625 --> 30:18.208
High opinion of yourself.

30:19.250 --> 30:22.167
- All right. A man-at-arms then.
- Mmm.

30:23.833 --> 30:25.875
Is this amusement for you, or...

30:26.958 --> 30:28.042
self-soothing?

30:29.000 --> 30:32.500
Categorizing the sharks
that might one day tear you apart.

30:35.958 --> 30:38.167
Now that is
a very good question, Dr. Glenn.

30:42.375 --> 30:45.083
Oh, no. I would like to make a toast.

30:47.625 --> 30:49.166
To Wilson Fisk

30:49.167 --> 30:52.791
and his incredibly hardworking
and ambitious staff.

30:52.792 --> 30:56.416
To the incredible work
you've done for the city

30:56.417 --> 30:57.583
and the port.

30:58.542 --> 31:00.208
There's a saying in politics,

31:00.667 --> 31:02.874
- "You are the company you keep."
-  She tests you

31:02.875 --> 31:04.250
because she fears you.

31:04.792 --> 31:08.500
Mr. Fisk, you are
a formidable businessman.

31:09.125 --> 31:11.917
Let's raise our glass to Wilson Fisk.

31:12.542 --> 31:14.332
We got three more on the manifest!

31:14.333 --> 31:15.416
Hurry it up!

31:20.667 --> 31:22.791
Get a clamp on it!

31:22.792 --> 31:23.792
Hey.

31:25.208 --> 31:26.374
That it?

31:26.375 --> 31:28.082
Yeah, yeah, that's all.

31:28.083 --> 31:29.707
All right. Get back on the boat,

31:29.708 --> 31:31.958
and we'll pick you up
once the load is delivered.

31:32.458 --> 31:33.875
- Wait.
- What's the problem?

31:35.250 --> 31:36.833
We've been on the boat all night.

31:37.375 --> 31:40.042
We've done the job,
and we want to go back to our families.

31:40.708 --> 31:42.291
Why can't you pay and let us go?

31:42.292 --> 31:43.500
'Cause I fucking said so.

32:01.500 --> 32:02.832
<i>Mayor Fisk is tough.</i>

32:02.833 --> 32:05.124
<i>Hell, he's fighting
this weekend, isn't he?</i>

32:05.125 --> 32:07.499
<i>And the vigilantes are next.</i>

32:07.500 --> 32:09.042
<i>Thank you. Thank you so much.</i>

32:13.667 --> 32:15.167
No. No.

32:16.292 --> 32:19.083
You try cutting me off tonight,
Dougie, my friend,

32:19.458 --> 32:21.374
I'm gonna call the health department.

32:21.375 --> 32:24.875
I'm going to tell those people that
you have pizza rat

32:25.708 --> 32:27.874
smoking crack in your bathroom.

32:29.417 --> 32:31.333
You're fun when you lose, you know that?

32:31.625 --> 32:32.625
Yeah.

32:33.208 --> 32:34.333
From the gentleman.

32:38.042 --> 32:39.042
A gentleman?

32:42.375 --> 32:43.375
Thank you.

32:44.917 --> 32:45.917
Fuck!

33:03.750 --> 33:06.042
- Hello? Holy shit.
-  Stay there.

33:09.792 --> 33:10.875
I need your help.

33:12.000 --> 33:13.000
Okay, look...

33:13.875 --> 33:15.125
I'm a little bit drunk...

33:16.333 --> 33:18.166
and I've had a really bad day,

33:18.167 --> 33:20.417
and I cannot be dragged
into any of this...

33:21.083 --> 33:23.625
- Resistance bullshit.
- You're already in it, Kirsten.

33:24.375 --> 33:25.791
You met with Duquesne today.

33:25.792 --> 33:28.875
- Are you following me?
- I need you to tell me everything you saw.

33:35.958 --> 33:37.957
Well, they had me wear blackout goggles,

33:37.958 --> 33:39.750
so I didn't see...

33:40.667 --> 33:41.917
anything.

33:42.458 --> 33:43.583
I can work with that.

33:45.167 --> 33:48.041
<i>Overwatch, go ahead
and let us know what north side looks like</i>

33:48.042 --> 33:49.916
<i>when you get a chance, I'll be on five.</i>

33:49.917 --> 33:51.457
<i>Affirmative.</i>

34:48.333 --> 34:50.416
All locked in.
We're good to go.

34:50.417 --> 34:52.083
-  Really? Awesome.
- Yes. Yeah.

35:04.000 --> 35:06.124
Fuck!

35:52.958 --> 35:55.082
-  Please, help us!
-  Help me!

35:55.083 --> 35:57.249
-  Help me!
-  Help me, please!

36:08.625 --> 36:09.625
Down here!

36:14.042 --> 36:15.832
-  Help!
- Let's go, let's go.

36:17.208 --> 36:18.582
<i>Copy. We're on our way.</i>

36:18.583 --> 36:20.582
Gather everyone. They're coming. Let's go.

36:20.583 --> 36:22.166
They're coming! Let's go.

36:22.167 --> 36:23.375
Let's go! Follow me.

36:24.667 --> 36:25.957
This way. Let's go.

36:32.792 --> 36:33.792
Daredevil!

36:34.875 --> 36:37.749
-  Everyone back in your cell, now!
- Free as many as you can.

37:06.292 --> 37:07.457
Go, go!

37:15.625 --> 37:16.625
Come on.

37:23.917 --> 37:25.457
<i>Use lethal force. Go hot.</i>

37:29.583 --> 37:30.791
Everyone down!

37:34.333 --> 37:35.874
Fuck! Get down! Get down!

38:02.500 --> 38:03.500
Move!

38:05.500 --> 38:06.916
Secure the target.

38:06.917 --> 38:09.457
Secure it. The rest of you,
with me! Go, go!

38:09.458 --> 38:11.542
Copy.
Moving to the rendezvous.

38:13.500 --> 38:15.583
-  Come on, team. Come on!
-  Let's go!

38:17.333 --> 38:18.333
Shit.

38:18.500 --> 38:19.583
Shit!

38:20.292 --> 38:22.500
Shit, shit, shit, shit.

38:26.333 --> 38:27.333
How about that?

38:45.750 --> 38:46.750
Hey.

38:48.417 --> 38:49.417
Hey.

38:50.208 --> 38:53.167
Whoever the fuck you are,
come on out before I put holes in you.

38:58.083 --> 38:59.083
Don't shoot.

38:59.708 --> 39:01.833
I'm just a kid!

39:05.917 --> 39:06.917
You're Karen, right?

39:09.083 --> 39:10.583
You're on wanted posters.

39:10.958 --> 39:11.958
Who are you?

39:12.500 --> 39:13.625
I'm Angela Del Toro.

39:14.208 --> 39:15.292
My aunt's in there.

39:16.083 --> 39:17.291
Daredevil's here, right?

39:17.292 --> 39:19.207
- No. You gotta go home.
- No.

39:19.208 --> 39:21.207
No. No! No! Come here! Take a look.

39:28.500 --> 39:29.667
Just take a look.

39:34.625 --> 39:36.374
I snagged some of their comms, too.

39:36.375 --> 39:38.332
<i>The rest of you, with me. Go!</i>

39:38.333 --> 39:40.000
<i>- Let's go!</i>
- I came here to help.

39:45.250 --> 39:46.333
Someone has to.

39:47.333 --> 39:49.292
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

39:49.958 --> 39:51.624
<i>Red team, red team,</i>

39:51.625 --> 39:52.791
come in, channel four.

39:52.792 --> 39:55.874
<i>Red team, red team, come in.
Red team, come in, channel four.</i>

39:55.875 --> 39:57.374
Fisk has people in here,

39:57.375 --> 39:59.542
<i>not just vigilantes.
I'm bringing them out now.</i>

40:00.250 --> 40:01.541
- Hello?
- Okay, let's go.

40:01.542 --> 40:02.874
Follow me!

40:02.875 --> 40:03.957
Shit!

40:03.958 --> 40:05.708
- Hello? What?
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

40:07.292 --> 40:08.292
I've got an idea.

40:09.667 --> 40:11.416
- Come on, move! Go. Let's go.
- Okay.

40:11.417 --> 40:12.582
Go, go, go.

40:12.583 --> 40:13.583
Go!

40:20.583 --> 40:21.833
Take cover! Take cover!

40:28.292 --> 40:30.041
-  <i>Shoot the prisoners!</i>
-  <i>What?</i>

40:30.042 --> 40:31.166
<i>Shoot the prisoners!</i>

40:31.167 --> 40:32.999
- Down! Everybody, down!
-  Shoot!

40:33.000 --> 40:34.833
Down!

40:38.583 --> 40:39.583
Down, get down!

40:48.667 --> 40:49.957
Hold, hold.

40:49.958 --> 40:51.375
- Friendlies.
-  Stand down.

40:53.000 --> 40:54.792
It's okay! It's okay! It's okay!

40:57.250 --> 40:58.332
- Get in!
- Now, now, go!

40:58.333 --> 41:00.000
Go, go, go! Stay down!

41:05.417 --> 41:07.666
-  Stay down!
- Light 'em up! Light 'em up!

41:07.667 --> 41:09.417
Get down!

41:12.250 --> 41:13.542
Let's go! Let's go!

41:15.250 --> 41:16.333
<i>Mija!</i>

41:18.667 --> 41:20.375
I love you. Okay, go, now, go.

41:21.750 --> 41:24.041
Let's go! Hurry! Come on!

41:30.083 --> 41:31.541
Everybody, out!

41:31.542 --> 41:32.791
<i>Move in! Move in!</i>

41:32.792 --> 41:34.541
<i>There's nowhere else for them to go.</i>

41:44.833 --> 41:46.167
Let's go! Move, move!

41:47.583 --> 41:48.750
Can you drive this thing?

41:49.792 --> 41:51.833
- I can try.
- Okay.

41:55.458 --> 41:57.042
Go, go, go! Go, go, go!

41:58.792 --> 41:59.875
Bloody hell.

42:03.417 --> 42:05.375
- Go, go, go! Let's go.
-  Everyone, sit down.

42:05.833 --> 42:07.749
- Stay calm.
- We'll get you safe.

42:07.750 --> 42:08.750
I know a place.

42:09.583 --> 42:10.583
Okay.

42:13.125 --> 42:15.375
Okay, all right.

42:18.917 --> 42:19.917
Move!

42:29.792 --> 42:30.958
Fuck it! Fuck it! Go!

42:42.458 --> 42:43.458
Fuck!

43:05.000 --> 43:07.582
I couldn't leave
those people there.

43:07.583 --> 43:10.167
I know.

43:11.875 --> 43:14.541
He got inside, and he had a lot of help.

43:14.542 --> 43:15.832
Cargo?

43:15.833 --> 43:17.166
<i>Safe in Red Hook.</i>

43:17.167 --> 43:18.292
The night crew?

43:18.625 --> 43:20.250
<i>Still onboard the</i> Northern Star.

43:26.042 --> 43:27.042
Good.

43:27.292 --> 43:28.500
We can use that.

43:31.833 --> 43:33.083
You know what to do.

43:33.792 --> 43:34.958
